text: Kalchreuth is a municipality in the district of Erlangen-Höchstadt, in Bavaria, Germany. It is 10 kilometers east of Erlangen and 15 kilometers north of Nuremberg and contains the villages of Kalchreuth, Käswasser and Röckenhof and also the hamlets of Stettenberg, Minderleinsmühle and Gabermühle. == Twin towns == * La Chapelle-des-Fougeretz (France), since 1993 ==References== Category:Erlangen-Höchstadt
title: Kalchreuth
